<TITLE> B. League likely in August </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 12 (bdnews24.com) - The Bangladesh Football Federation (BFF) plans to bring the B. League forward in August instead of September following requests from the professional football league clubs. "We had a nice discussion with the club representatives and we are satisfied," BFF president Kazi Salahuddin told reporters emerging from the meeting at the BFF House Monday. Salahuddin said that the cubs in the meeting gave them some advice of which some were logical and some were less logical, but they wanted to shape those advices in a uniform string. The former football star said that they had promised the clubs to distribute 70 percent of sponsorship money among them and they would sit with sponsor Prime Bank Tuesday. The BFF boss also said that both parties stuck to their promised player transfers from May 15 to June 20. BFF senior vice president Salam Murshidi, also chairman of the B. League committee, said that the clubs had asked them to ensure good playgrounds and accommodation. BFF vice president and B. League vice-chairman Kazi Nabil Ahmed also spoke on the occasion. Nabil confirmed that he had wanted release as the team leader of the national team in the SAFF Championship due to his business involvements. He said that he had also decided to stay in the B. League committee as the BFF president relied on him. On May 7, Nabil asked the federation to release him from both posts of team manager and vice-chairman of B. League. 
